author: Rachel Kaser
title: Prince’s music finally returns to streaming services this Sunday
text:
74 shares 
Music fans missing the late singer Prince, rejoice! On Sunday, some of his music finally returns to popular music streaming sites. 
Starting on February 12 – also the date of the Grammys – Prince’s music will be available through a number of streaming services. Among those confirmed are Spotify, iHeartRadio, Apple Music , Amazon Music, and Napster.
